The paper deals with causal discovery, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on identifying causal graphs using functional models suggests that the paper is most likely to be classified under the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of conditional independence-based methods also suggests that the paper could be classified under the information theory (cs.IT) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the practical algorithm and experiments on simulated data suggest that the paper could also be classified under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
